# 🚀 BAH 2026 — Render.com Deployment Guide

**Status**: ✅ App tested locally, **all checks pass**. Ready to deploy.

---

## Quick Summary

| Item | Value |
|---|---|
| Current model | v5 (ResNet-50, 2048-D) |
| Gallery | 9200 vectors, 256-D |
| Modalities | ms / optical / sar |
| Classes | 14 |
| Average retrieval time | ~0.02 ms |
| Expected P@5 | ~98.6% |

---

## ⚠️ Pre-requisite (one-time)

### 1. GitHub account
- Already have one? Skip.
- Sign up: https://github.com/signup (2 min)

### 2. Render.com account
- Sign up: https://render.com (3 min)
- **Sign up with GitHub** (easiest)

---

## Step-by-step Deployment (15-20 min total)

### Step 1: GitHub pe naya repo banao

1. Browser: https://github.com/new
2. Fill:
   - **Repository name**: `bah2026-cross-modal`
   - **Description**: `Cross-Modal Satellite Image Retrieval — BAH 2026`
   - **Public** ← important (free plan limitation)
   - ✅ Add a README file
   - ✅ Add .gitignore → Python
3. Click **Create repository**
4. Note the URL: `https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/bah2026-cross-modal`

---

### Step 2: Code push karo GitHub pe

PowerShell me ye commands chalao (replace `YOUR_USERNAME`):

```powershell
cd D:\BAH2026\cross_modal_retrieval

# Init git
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit — BAH 2026 deployment"

# Connect to GitHub
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/bah2026-cross-modal.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

**Push karne pe credentials maange**:
- Username: tumhara GitHub username
- Password: **Personal Access Token** (not password!)

**Token kaise banaye**:
1. https://github.com/settings/tokens
2. **Generate new token** → **classic** → scopes me `repo` tick karo
3. **Generate** → token copy karo (ek baar dikhega)
4. Ye password ki jagah paste karo

---

### Step 3: Render pe deploy

1. Browser: https://render.com → Sign in (GitHub se)
2. Dashboard pe **"New +"** button click → **"Web Service"**
3. **"Connect a repository"** section me:
   - **GitHub account connect** karo (first time)
   - `bah2026-cross-modal` repo select karo
4. **Settings page khulega**:
   - **Name**: `bah2026-cross-modal` (URL me use hoga)
   - **Region**: Oregon (ya closest)
   - **Branch**: main
   - **Runtime**: **Docker** ← select karo
   - **Dockerfile Path**: `./Dockerfile` (auto-detected)
   - **Plan**: **Free** ← select karo
5. **"Advanced"** expand karo:
   - **Health Check Path**: `/api/health`
   - **Auto-Deploy**: **Yes** (default)
6. **"Create Web Service"** click karo

---

### Step 4: Wait for build (5-10 min)

Render log dikhayega:
```
==> Building...
[+] Building 245.3s (15/15) FINISHED
==> Uploading...
==> Deploying...
==> Your service is live 🎉
```

**Live URL** milega:
```
https://bah2026-cross-modal.onrender.com
```

---

### Step 5: Test karo

1. Browser me URL kholo
2. Page load hona chahiye with upload UI
3. Test image upload karo (e.g. EuroSAT/Forest/s2/Forest_5.jpg)
4. Top-5/10 results aane chahiye ~50-100 ms me

**Ye bhi test karo**:
- https://bah2026-cross-modal.onrender.com/api/health
  → JSON response with gallery info

---

## ⚠️ Common Issues & Solutions

### Issue: Build fails "out of memory"
- Free tier me 512 MB RAM hai
- Dockerfile me `torch` install karte time bahut RAM lagta hai
- Solution: Already optimized. Agar phir bhi fail ho, Render pe **paid plan** (7$/mo) use karo

### Issue: Service "sleeps" after 15 min inactivity
- Free tier limitation
- First request after sleep ~30 sec lagta hai (cold start)
- Demo ke liye theek hai

### Issue: Large model loading slow on free tier
- 28 MB projector + 51 MB features load honge
- ~30-60 sec startup time
- `/api/health` endpoint ready hone pe healthy mark hoga

### Issue: Git push fails "repository not found"
- Repo URL check karo
- Personal Access Token use karo (password nahi)

### Issue: "Dockerfile not found"
- Repo root me Dockerfile hona chahiye
- `.dockerignore` me jo exclude kiya woh Dockerfile ke neeche wala code nahi hona chahiye

---

## 🎯 Important Files (deployment me include hote hain)

```
cross_modal_retrieval/
├── Dockerfile              ← Render uses this
├── render.yaml             ← service config (optional)
├── .dockerignore           ← exclude junk
├── requirements.txt        ← Python deps
├── src/                    ← backbone, projector, dataset code
├── webapp/
│   ├── app.py              ← Flask backend
│   ├── static/             ← CSS/JS
│   └── templates/index.html
└── outputs/
    ├── projector.pt        ← v5 weights (28 MB)
    ├── gallery.faiss       ← FAISS index (10 MB)
    ├── gallery_meta.npz    ← metadata (9 MB)
    └── features.npz        ← features cache (51 MB)
```

---

## 🔄 Future: Model Update

Jab tum Colab pe v6 train kar lo:
1. Download `cross_modal_v6.zip` from Colab
2. Extract: `v6_projector.pt`, `v6_gallery.faiss`, `v6_gallery_meta.npz`
3. Rename and replace in `outputs/`
4. `git add outputs/ && git commit -m "v6 weights" && git push`
5. Render **auto-deploy** karega (5-10 min)

